Name: Nepal Consumer Price Index Inflation Rate
Metadata: Notes: The National Urban Consumer Price Index (NUCPI) measures the change in the level of prices of a fixed basket of consumer goods and services. The index refers to urban areas defined as government municipalities (about 13 percent of total population) and represents urban households excluding households falling on the first, second, ninth, and tenth income deciles; single person households and households with more than eight persons; households obtaining more than 50 percent of consumption from own production or sources other than market purchases; and households receiving less than 50 percent of their income in cash. Separate indices for Kathmandu valley, urban Hills, and urban Terai (southern plain land) are also compiled. The index reference period is fiscal year 1995/96 (starts in mid July). The composition of the present CPI basket is derived from the household budget survey in urban areas conducted over the twelve-month period, mid-July 1995 Ã¢â‚¬“ mid-July 1996, and with a sample size of 2500 households representing 0.8 percent of urban households. The consumer basket consists of 301 items of goods and services grouped into 17 major consumption groups and sub-groups
